 &lt;h2 id=&#34;How-AI-Makes-Me-a-Better-Programmer&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#How-AI-Makes-Me-a-Better-Programmer&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;How AI Makes Me a Better Programmer&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;How AI Makes Me a Better Programmer&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;Not-what-you-think&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Not-what-you-think&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Not what you think&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Not what you think&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;At least I hope it isnâ€™t otherwise why bother writing this?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most people probably think that when I say AI makes me a better programmer that it makes me more efficient. That I can get more done with less effort. And while that is also true, I find that AI has forced me to become a better programmer in ways that will continue to benefit me even if AI is just a fad and we all start writing code by hand tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;
