&lt;h2 id=&#34;Decorators&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Decorators&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Decorators&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Decorators&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;I donâ€™t want to spend a lot of time on decorators. Â If youâ€™ve been using .NET, youâ€™ll recognized decorators as â€œAttributesâ€. Java programmers are probably used to calling them annotations. &lt;/p&gt;
