&lt;p&gt;My story is similar to many from my generation. I learned a little Basic to catch the programming bug. Then I tried Pascal and moved on to C before I went back to school where I learned COBOL, JCL and CICS. Mostly it was COBOL. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It didnâ€™t take long to learn any of those languages because the language was the language. Things didnâ€™t move quickly. CICS was simple. And we only needed enough JCL to get our programs to compile. &lt;figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/uploads/2018/03/2018-03-06.jpg&#34; title=&#34;The Full Stack Developer Myth&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;Photo credit: &lt;a href=&#34;//visualhunt.com/author/751f9f&#34;&gt;Avariel Falcon&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=&#34;//visualhunt.com/re/1f7533&#34;&gt;Visual hunt&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#x2F; &lt;a href=&#34;//creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/&#34;&gt; CC BY&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
