&lt;h2 id=&#34;A-Community-of-Hacks&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#A-Community-of-Hacks&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;A Community of Hacks?&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;A Community of Hacks?&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are we just a community of hacks?Â  I think maybe we are. All we care about is that weâ€™ve shipped some code. We, largely, donâ€™t care about our craft.Â  If we were artist, we starve.Â  Not because artist starve (which is a myth by the way) but because the code we produce is so crappy, no one would consider it valuable. &lt;/p&gt;
