&lt;h2 id=&#34;karma-conf-js&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#karma-conf-js&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;karma.conf.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;karma.conf.js&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To run your tests, youâ€™ll need a &lt;code&gt;karma.conf.js&lt;/code&gt; file in your root directory.Â  Again, the easiest thing to do is to copy this file over from a project you created with the Angular CLI.&lt;/p&gt;
