&lt;p&gt;You can name the member variables whatever you want.Â  They never get used.Â  &lt;code&gt;ofType()&lt;/code&gt; is a filter that makes the observable stuff only fire for that particular type. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The magic happens in the &lt;code&gt;Observable.timer(1).take(1)&lt;/code&gt;.Â  Here we wait for one millisecond, take the first item out of the stream and immediately close the observable.Â  Once that completes, the &lt;code&gt;map()&lt;/code&gt; returns a new action. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every Effect must return an action or you must tell the Effect that it wonâ€™t return an action.Â  Notice that we donâ€™t dispatch the action.Â  That is done by NgRX for us.Â  We just return the action. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To tell an Effect that no action will be returned, pass &lt;code&gt;&amp;#123;dispatch: false&amp;#125;&lt;/code&gt; into &lt;code&gt;@Effect()&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
