&lt;p&gt;The first definition may look a bit odd. Â We are setting up a route to page1, but the route is the children. Â Then in the children we define a route to â€˜â€™. Â This is where the Page1Component is specified as the component we want to load. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also note that we specified &lt;code&gt;pathMatch: &amp;#39;full&amp;#39;&lt;/code&gt; for the Page1Component. Â This is because we only want this component to be loaded when the child path is empty. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using this definition, everything loads into the top level router-outlet. Â If we placed Page1Component at the same level as we defined the page1 path, then Angular would expect to have a router-outlet in Page1Component where Pag1SubpageComponent would be loaded. &lt;/p&gt;
