&lt;h3 id=&#34;Forms&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Forms&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Forms&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Forms&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Iâ€™ve found that the best way to work with forms is to create a structure in my entity that maps directly to my form.Â So, if I have a form with firstName, lastName, and birthDate, Iâ€™ll define my form in my template with a form group using firstName, lastName, and birthDate as formControlName values.&lt;/p&gt;
