&lt;h2 id=&#34;What-are-Template-Driven-Forms&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#What-are-Template-Driven-Forms&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;What are Template Driven Forms&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What are Template Driven Forms&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;For those who arenâ€™t already familiar with the terms, letâ€™s define them first.Â  A template driven form is an Angular form that has most of the form logic in the template code.Â  The elements that give away the fact that we are working with a template driven form are that we are using ngModel in our form fields, all of our form fields have a name attribute, and our form has ngForm declared as assigned to the form variable.&lt;/p&gt;
