&lt;p&gt;But other than the fact that there is less code in the template and we can handle everything about the form in our TypeScript, the main difference between Template Driven Forms and Model Driven Forms is that Model Driven Forms let us treat the form as a whole rather than individual parts.Â This solves problems that used to be rather tricky using Template Driven Forms.&lt;/p&gt;
