&lt;h2 id=&#34;Easy-Change-Detection&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Easy-Change-Detection&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Easy Change Detection&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Easy Change Detection&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you are working with Template Driven Forms, you know that the way you know a value in a control has changed is because the property it is associated with gets a new value.Â Setting up a simple setter lets you know the field has changed.Â Or if you prefer you can use the split syntax of&lt;/p&gt;
