&lt;h2 id=&#34;What-would-it-be-like-if-â€¦&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#What-would-it-be-like-if-â€¦&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;What would it be like if â€¦&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What would it be like if â€¦&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Just imagine with me what it would be like if nothing ever changed.Â  How far back do you want to go?Â  How about back to where I started programming.Â  OK, that was 29 years ago.Â  I started programming on DOS 3.1 using Clipper (thatâ€™s a dBase III compiler).Â  We had 640K (thatâ€™s 640,000 bytes, not megs, not gigs) to program in.Â  We used overlay tricks to cram programs that were three times that size into the computer.Â  There was no GUI and what graphics we did have were incredibly grainy.Â  You were lucky if you had color.Â  There was no Internet, that was still the â€œpropertyâ€ of the colleges and the universities.Â  No Google to find answers to your questions.Â  No blogs.&lt;/p&gt;
