&lt;p&gt;There has also been a move to avoid estimates entirely.Â  The argument goes something along the lines of, â€œwe know the least about a project at the beginning of the project, so we canâ€™t really give an accurate estimate.â€Â  Which is mostly true.Â  And yet, there are people who need to know â€œhow much is this going to cost?â€Â  What do we do for them?Â  How do we balance the two realities? And then all of this lead me to think of all the ways we sabotage our estimates, or our estimates are sabotaged for us.&lt;/p&gt;
